HEADWORD: Samshu
<hw>Sam"shu</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chinese <ets>san-shao</ets> thrice fired.]</ety>
<def>A spirituous liquor distilled by the Chinese from the yeasty liquor
in which boiled rice has fermented under pressure.</def> <rj><au>S. W.
Williams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
